<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Information Page</title>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Information Page</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>About This Document</h2>
            <p>This document provides a basic example of how to structure information using HTML.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Key Information Points</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Point 1:</strong> HTML uses tags to define content.</li>
                <li><strong>Point 2:</strong> The `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration defines the document type.</li>
                <li><strong>Point 3:</strong> The `<html>` element is the root element of an HTML page.</li>
                <li><strong>Point 4:</strong> The `<head>` element contains meta-information about the HTML page.</li>
                <li><strong>Point 5:</strong> The `<body>` element contains the visible page content.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Example of Code</h2>
            <pre><code>
&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;This is a heading.&lt;/h1&gt;
            </code></pre>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 Information Creator</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
